The use of rational approximations and solving asymmetric linear systems also suggests that it could belong to the cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves working with data matrices, which could place it in the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The use of principal component projection and regression also suggests that it could belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves solving linear systems, which is a common problem in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category.
